Talent Summary

Key Strengths

Scott is one of the team members who is most synonymous with the unique culture in NAFS. I view his key strengths as:

Comfort and capability flexing between Marketing and Sales

Project management - with the caveat that he sometimes takes on too much, but when priorities are clear and achievable, he excels in leading project teams, timelines and deliverables

Culture building - hes a selfless team player who embraces whatever he can do to help his teammates and the business

Development Opportunities

Scotts most notable development area is in strategic thought leadership. He struggles to articulate a vision and make tough choices in support of it. To demonstrate potential in this area, and to benefit his function and his career development, he is tasked with two assignments by the end of F25: developing a NAFS eComm Overview and a Customer Marketing Vision.

 

I believe Scott has made tangible and admirable progress in two development areas that were called out in this space one year ago - team leadership and control of his career destiny.
